svg.text: The Kregel Windmill Museum in Nebraska City is “a time capsule of early 20th Century shop-type manufacturing” while the Bartels Museum and Marxhausen Gallery in Seward covers both natural history with minerals and fossils as well as an art gallery promoting cultural experiences and is home to the Koenig Collection.
The Johnson County Courthouse in Tecumseh is the centerpiece of the community’s architecturally rich downtown historic square.
